{
  "quotes": [
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0001",
      "block_id": "B011",
      "text": "Ms. Gordon met for lunch, during which meeting Ms. Gordon advised Mr. Malkoski of Ingredions interest in acquiring Penford. Ms. Gordon noted that the business strategies of Ingredion and Penford were similar, with both"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0002",
      "block_id": "B015",
      "text": "Subsequently, Penford and Ingredion executed a Secrecy Agreement, effective as of July 20, 2014, providing for limited exchange of"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0003",
      "block_id": "B019",
      "text": "as the Companys financial advisor and to advise on shareholder matters and to evaluate strategic alternatives, and directed management to negotiate a suitable engagement letter. An engagement letter with Deutsche Bank was executed on"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0004",
      "block_id": "B019",
      "text": "several firms and reported on interview meetings management had with certain firms regarding a potential engagement. Following discussion of potential financial advisors, the Executive Committee directed management to proceed to retain Deutsche Bank"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0005",
      "block_id": "B024",
      "text": "submit a proposal to acquire the Company. Mr. Fortnum suggested that a price of $17.00 per share on a fully diluted basis could likely get support from Ingredions board. Mr. Malkoski responded that, in his opinion, the proposed price"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0006",
      "block_id": "B025",
      "text": "letter from Mr. Fortnum, confirming Ingredions interest in a possible business combination between Ingredion and the Company, citing certain strategic reasons for the proposed acquisition, and providing an indicative valuation of $18.00 per share in cash for all of the outstanding capital stock of Penford on a fully diluted basis. Based on the $12.10 per share closing price of Penfords common stock on August 8, 2014, the last business day prior to receiving this"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0007",
      "block_id": "B030",
      "text": "proposal was non-binding, Ingredion appeared to be a credible and financially capable buyer with clear strategic reasons for acquiring the Company. Deutsche Bank then provided the board with information and insights on Ingredion, and reviewed with"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0008",
      "block_id": "B029",
      "text": "discussed Party As potential interest in acquiring or combining with Penford. Party A noted that it saw value in Penford but only at a typical takeover premium based on current trading price, due to the fact that it would base any offer price"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0009",
      "block_id": "B046",
      "text": "September 9, 2014, Party A expressed interest in having further discussions regarding a transaction and Deutsche Bank forwarded Party A a nondisclosure and standstill agreement. Also on September 9, 2014, another strategic counterparty"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0010",
      "block_id": "B046",
      "text": "contacted by Deutsche Bank (referred to as Party B) expressed interest in further discussions, and Deutsche Bank forwarded a nondisclosure and standstill agreement to proceed with additional discussions with Party B."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0011",
      "block_id": "B047",
      "text": "On September 10, 2014, a third potential strategic counterparty contacted by Deutsche Bank (referred to as Party C) expressed interest in pursuing a transaction, and Deutsche Bank forwarded Party C a nondisclosure and standstill agreement on September 11, 2014. Also on September 10, 2014, Mr. Malkoski, Mr. Fortnum and Mr. Saucier had a telephone conversation"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0012",
      "block_id": "B048",
      "text": "On September 11, 2014, a fourth potential strategic counterparty contacted by Deutsche Bank (referred to as Party D) expressed interest, and Deutsche Bank forwarded a nondisclosure and standstill agreement to Party D."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0013",
      "block_id": "B051",
      "text": "On September 15, 2014, Penford and Party C executed a nondisclosure and standstill agreement, which included standard confidentiality"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0014",
      "block_id": "B053",
      "text": "that Ingredion could potentially increase its proposal from $18.00 to $18.25 or $18.50 per share on a fully diluted basis. Based on the $14.70 per share closing price of Penfords common stock on September 16, 2014, the last business day"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0015",
      "block_id": "B056",
      "text": "On September 23, 2014, Penford and Party D executed a nondisclosure and standstill agreement, which included standard confidentiality"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0016",
      "block_id": "B064",
      "text": "On September 30, 2014, Penford and Party A executed a nondisclosure and standstill agreement, which included standard confidentiality"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0017",
      "block_id": "B066",
      "text": "Mr. Fortnum then stated that Ingredion was prepared to move forward based on a proposed price of $18.50 per share on a fully diluted basis. Mr. Malkoski responded that that price was unlikely to be high enough for Penfords board of"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0018",
      "block_id": "B067",
      "text": "its indication of interest and increasing the proposed price to $19.00 per share of outstanding Penford capital stock on a fully diluted basis. Based on the $12.77 per share closing price of Penfords common stock on October 1, 2014, the"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0019",
      "block_id": "B072",
      "text": "Ingredions legal counsel. On October 4, Deutsche Bank followed up with Party A regarding the potential transaction with Penford, pursuant to which Party A indicated any offer would be below $17.50 - $18.00 per share in cash. Deutsche Bank"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0020",
      "block_id": "B076",
      "text": "Also on October 8, 2014, Deutsche Bank met with representatives from Party D, who indicated that it did not intend to move forward with discussions regarding a potential transaction involving the Company."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0021",
      "block_id": "B085",
      "text": "transaction had been reduced from $17.50 - $18.00 per share to $16.00 - $18.00 per share, due to increased volatility in the markets."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0022",
      "block_id": "B087",
      "text": "On October 14, 2014, Mr. Fortnum called Mr. Malkoski to confirm the proposed price of $19.00 and discuss finalizing the draft"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0023",
      "block_id": "B089",
      "text": "Later on October 14, 2014, Party A provided a formal letter with its indication of interest with respect to an acquisition of the Company"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0024",
      "block_id": "B089",
      "text": "at a price of $16.00 per share, citing increased volatility in the markets as the reason for the decrease in the offer price. Based on the $11.07 per share closing price of Penfords common stock as of October 13, 2014, the day immediately"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0025",
      "block_id": "B095",
      "text": "During the evening on October 14, 2014, Penford and Ingredion finalized and executed the merger agreement, and Penford, Ingredion and SEACOR executed the voting and support agreement. Penford and Ingredion issued press releases announcing the transaction on October 15, 2014 prior to the opening of trading."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0026",
      "block_id": "B095",
      "text": "agreement, and Penford, Ingredion and SEACOR executed the voting and support agreement. Penford and Ingredion issued press releases announcing the transaction on October 15, 2014 prior to the opening of trading."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0027",
      "block_id": "B021",
      "text": "On July 30, 2014, the board of directors held a special meeting primarily for the purpose"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0028",
      "block_id": "B010",
      "text": "July 11, 2014, SEACOR filed an amendment to its Schedule 13D (referred to as the SEACOR Filing) with the Securities and Exchange Commission (referred to as the SEC) in which SEACOR stated its intent to nominate four candidates for election as"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0029",
      "block_id": "B022",
      "text": "On August 1, 2014, a representative acting on behalf of a company in the industry (referred to as Party A) sent Mr. Malkoski an"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0030",
      "block_id": "B046",
      "text": "contacted by Deutsche Bank (referred to as Party B) expressed interest in further discussions, and Deutsche Bank forwarded a nondisclosure and standstill agreement to proceed with additional discussions with Party B."
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0031",
      "block_id": "B047",
      "text": "On September 10, 2014, a third potential strategic counterparty contacted by Deutsche Bank (referred to as Party C) expressed interest in"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0032",
      "block_id": "B048",
      "text": "On September 11, 2014, a fourth potential strategic counterparty contacted by Deutsche Bank (referred to as Party D) expressed interest,"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0033",
      "block_id": "B050",
      "text": "Also on September 12, 2014, Deutsche Bank left a voicemail for another strategic counterparty (referred to as Party E) regarding a"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0034",
      "block_id": "B058",
      "text": "transaction with Penford was not particularly strong. The board also discussed with management and Deutsche Bank whether the two largest companies in Penfords industry (referred to as Party F and Party G) should be approached regarding a"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0035",
      "block_id": "B005",
      "text": "In 2007 and 2009, the Company received unsolicited indications of interest to acquire Penford from two parties engaged in the Companys"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0036",
      "block_id": "B019",
      "text": "Committee, as well as certain other directors, members of Penfords management and representatives of Perkins Coie LLP (referred to as Perkins Coie), Penfords legal counsel, were present. At the meeting, members of management updated the"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0037",
      "block_id": "B037",
      "text": "other members of Ingredions senior management and representatives of J. P. Morgan Securities, Ingredions financial advisor. This presentation provided information regarding Penfords operations, corporate strategy, business segments,"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0038",
      "block_id": "B072",
      "text": "Later on October 3, 2014, Perkins Coie sent a revised draft of the merger agreement to Sidley Austin LLP (referred to as Sidley Austin),"
    },
    {
      "quote_id": "Q0039",
      "block_id": "B074",
      "text": "On October 7, 2014, Perkins Coie contacted Milbank, Tweed, Hadley & McCloy, LLP (referred to as Milbank), legal counsel to"
    }
  ],
